      exact h₃
```

Here, we change `l1` to `l₁` (with subscript 1), etc., in the `have` statement so that we don't shadow the outer variables. 

But this is fine because Lean allows this. 

In fact, Lean will treat `{l₁}` and `{l1}` as different variables, even though they look similar in Unicode. 

But there is no real issue in Lean because you can have both `l1` (ASCII) and `l₁` (Unicode) as variables, and Lean will consider them different names.

